> And for the uninitiated... they will also fit 1970 buses.  
> Modifications necessary may include brake line changes (if 
> you upgrade to the vacuum boosted braking system)/steering 
> box bracket relocation(unless you plan to upgrade from the 
> peg-and-roller steering  to the later version).  I believe the '68
> transporter has a different location for its beam mounting holes.  
> Is '69 the same as '70?  I bought one of Ron's beams from the last 
> round of sales, and I'm looking forward to a tight, new 
> suspension/brakes/steering again!


According to the archives, '68 and '69 are the same (and have different
mounting bracket spacing from '70 up). I couldn't confirm this from
personal experience, though.

